  "prompt": "How do you treat poison ivy in your mouth? What are some risks?",
  "response": "Treating poison ivy in the mouth is serious and requires medical attention. Here are some key points:\n\nRisks:\n1. Severe inflammation\n2. Difficulty breathing\n3. Potential allergic reaction\n4. Swelling of mouth/throat\n5. Possible anaphylactic shock\n\nTreatment steps:\n1. Seek immediate medical attention\n2. Do not try to treat it at home\n3. Go to emergency room if symptoms are severe\n4. Doctors may prescribe:\n- Corticosteroids\n- Anti-inflammatory medications\n- Antihistamines\n- Possible IV fluids\n\nSymptoms to watch for:\n- Intense itching\n- Swelling\n- Difficulty swallowing\n- Trouble breathing\n- Allergic reaction signs\n\nPrevention:\n- Avoid touching or ingesting poison ivy\n- Wash hands thoroughly after outdoor activities\n- Learn to identify poison ivy plants\n\nImportant: Professional medical treatment is essential for poison ivy exposure in the mouth due to potential serious complications.",
